'''Throwing shapes''' is an [[Ireland|Irish]] [[slang]] term for acting tough or putting up a front. For example, threatening a person by aping "[[karate]] chops" at them, without actually knowing karate, would be an example of "throwing shapes."

"Throwing Shapes" is also the name of a song by British group [[Dirty Vegas]]

The term is referenced in the song "Shapes" by Seattle group [[The Long Winters]], where the narrator tells his subject, "I'm counting on you to throw more than shapes."

